🧠 OS Concept 1: Fork & Exec
1️⃣ Simple Idea

👉 fork() = create a new process
👉 exec() = replace process with a new program

🧠 Real-World Analogy

Imagine:

You clone yourself 👥 → fork
Then one clone changes job → exec
⚙️ Why It Exists

OS needs to:

create new processes
run different programs
⚙️ How fork() Works
int pid = fork();

After fork:

Parent Process
Child Process (copy)

Both run same code but have different:

👉 PID (Process ID)

⚙️ How exec() Works
exec("new_program");

👉 Current process is replaced completely

🔗 Connection to Process (Day 1)
fork → creates new process
exec → loads new program into process
🎯 Placement Question

Q: Difference between fork and exec?

👉 fork = creates new process
👉 exec = replaces process program

🧠 Memory Trick
fork = copy
exec = execute new
🧠 OS Concept 2: Zombie Process
1️⃣ Simple Idea

Zombie =
👉 process that has finished execution but still exists in process table

🧠 Real-World Analogy

Student finished exam but:

👉 result not collected yet

Still in system.

⚙️ Why It Happens

When:

1️⃣ Child process finishes
2️⃣ Parent does NOT read its status

👉 child becomes zombie

⚙️ What It Contains

Only:

PID
Exit status

(No memory, no execution)

⚙️ How to Remove

Parent must call:

wait()
🔗 Connection to PCB

Zombie still has entry in:

👉 Process Control Block (PCB)

🎯 Placement Question

Q: What is zombie process?

👉 A terminated process whose entry remains in process table.

🧠 Memory Trick
Zombie = dead but still present
⚙️ COA Concept 3: RISC vs CISC

🔥 VERY COMMON INTERVIEW QUESTION

1️⃣ Simple Idea

Two types of CPU design:

👉 RISC = simple instructions
👉 CISC = complex instructions

🧠 Real-World Analogy
RISC

👉 Many simple steps

Like:

Pick → Cut → Cook → Serve
CISC

👉 One complex step

"Prepare full dish"
⚙️ Differences
Feature	RISC	CISC
Instructions	simple	complex
Speed	faster	slower
Memory	more	less
Examples	ARM	x86
⚙️ Why RISC is Faster

Because:

👉 simpler instructions → faster execution → better pipelining

🔗 Connection to Pipelining (Day 4)

RISC works better with:

👉 pipelining

🎯 Placement Question

Q: Difference between RISC and CISC?

👉 RISC = simple, fast
👉 CISC = complex, fewer instructions

🧠 Memory Trick
RISC = Reduced
CISC = Complex
⚙️ COA Concept 4: Performance Metrics

🔥 VERY IMPORTANT FOR INTERVIEW

1️⃣ Simple Idea

Performance =
👉 how fast a program runs

⚙️ Key Formula

CPU Time
=
Instruction Count
×
CPI
×
Clock Cycle Time
CPU Time=Instruction Count×CPI×Clock Cycle Time

🧠 Meaning
Instruction Count → number of instructions
CPI → cycles per instruction
Clock time → speed of CPU
⚙️ Important Terms
1️⃣ Throughput

👉 how many tasks per second

2️⃣ Latency

👉 time for one task

3️⃣ Clock Speed

👉 cycles per second

🔗 Connection to CPU

Performance improves when:

fewer instructions
lower CPI
faster clock
🎯 Placement Question

Q: How to improve CPU performance?

👉 reduce instruction count, CPI, or increase clock speed

🧠 Memory Trick
Performance = Work / Time
